<TITLE> Govt to form cell on acid violence </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 3 (bdnews24.com)The government is going to form a "national monitoring cell" to be tasked with reviewing the acid-violence related cases, the home minister said Sunday. A home ministry joint secretary will head the cell that will also provide financial assistance to prevent acid violence, treatment of acid victims and legal fight, Sahara Khatun said. "The cell will be extended to district level," she told reporters after a meeting of National Acid Violence Prevention Council in the capital. 
